## Decision

> I must **stop and not produce the completed dashboard this cycle.** A blocking contradiction surfaced during inspection that makes it unsafe to "slice and dice" the staged data into the template as-is. Status: **blocked**.
>
> **What the intent and manual asked me to do.** Per the MIS manual § Section 3 (Slice & Dice), Step 3 reads the clean staged dataset and fills the dashboard workbook — the KPI strip, monthly trend, asset/liability and channel-mix boxes, product performance, branch performance, the RM leaderboard, top-10 branches, and the five bound charts — reading product/branch/RM counts from the data itself, resizing data-driven sections and leaving structural ones (12 months, Asset/Liability, 3 channels, top-10 cap) filled-or-zero, and writing reconciliation totals as plain computed numbers.
>
> **Why I am blocking rather than filling.** Two independent, hard contradictions between what the prior cycle handed off and what actually exists on disk:
>
> **The single honest resolution.** The runtime's own ontology says status is *exactly one of validated or blocked, never a hedge*. I cannot certify this as validated, so it is blocked. Concretely: I do **not** write `outputs/bank_daily_sales_dashboard_2025_completed.xlsx` this cycle. The next operator must (a) reconcile the staged-dataset discrepancy — determine whether the 1000-row, region-bearing CSV is the true clean output and the prior cycle's 907-row report is stale, or vice versa, and re-run Steps 1–2 if they diverge; and (b) obtain a readable dump of the template's cell layout, section anchors, total rows and the five charts' series/category ranges before any cell is written. Only once the staged data's provenance is trustworthy and the template's fillable structure is actually known can Step 3 be executed faithfully. Reporting the fact without pretending the dashboard was built is the correct action here.

## Data

- status: blocked
- anomalies found: Not available — Step 3 was blocked before any sanity/validation check ran this cycle.
- reconciliation gap: Not available — no validated check was performed this cycle.
- headline kpis: Not available — the dashboard was not built, so no KPI values were computed.

## Explanation

> I stopped short of building the completed dashboard this cycle because inspection turned up two hard contradictions between what the previous cycle handed off and what's actually on disk — the staged dataset doesn't match (a 1000-row, region-bearing CSV versus the prior cycle's 907-row report), and I lack a readable dump of the template's cell layout, section anchors, total rows, and chart ranges — so filling the workbook would risk writing untrustworthy numbers into an unknown structure. Since the runtime requires a status of either validated or blocked with no middle ground, and I cannot honestly certify this as validated, I marked it blocked and did not write the output file; the next operator should first reconcile which staged dataset is authoritative (re-running Steps 1–2 if they diverge) and obtain the template's real layout before Step 3 is attempted.

